\frametitle{Symmetric Matrices}

If $A=A^T$, then $A$ is called a \textit{symmetric} matrix.

\begin{equation*}
    \begin{bmatrix}
        \phantom{-}5 & -2           & -1 \\
        -2           & \phantom{-}6 & -1 \\
        -1           & -1           & \phantom{-}3
    \end{bmatrix}
\end{equation*}

\begin{block}{Note}
    $B = A^T A$ is symmetric for any (real) matrix $A$.
\end{block}

